messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files containing the implementation of App\Http\Controllers\UserPasswordController@update (PUT|PATCH):
- app/Http/Controllers/UserPasswordController.php

Explanation:
- The route App\Http\Controllers\UserPasswordController@update (PUT|PATCH) is implemented in the UserPasswordController class, specifically in the update method found in app/Http/Controllers/UserPasswordController.php.
- The update method:
  - Accepts a UserPasswordsRequest for validation.
  - Retrieves the currently authenticated user and checks authorization with $this->authorize('update', $user).
  - Hashes the new password via Hash::make and merges it into the request data.
  - Updates the authenticated user with the new password using $user->update($request->only('password')).
  - Redirects back to the password settings page with a success message.
